forever the trio + 1

The army grows stronger....

I mainly play 4 key mania, but can also play standard pretty well (I think I'm a bit underranked currently, gotta get some more dank pp)


Me
I am an 18 year old kid who started playing VSRGs a loooooong time ago. I probably played DDR for the first time when I was maybe 5 years old, and I have always loved rhythm games since then. I moved from DDR to Guitar Hero around the time when I was 8 or 9 years old, got pretty good at it, then moved back to DDR. When I was in 11 or 12 I stopped playing VSRGs for some reason and didn't expect to get back into them until early my junior year in high school, when someone introduced me to a game called FlashFlashRevolution (in-game-name is also TheToaphster), and you got to go fast with both hands instead of just one like in guitar hero. I was immediately hooked and then at the beginning of my senior year I was told about osu! and osu!mania by one of my classmates, and boy am I glad to be here.

Now that I'm here I can talk about my development as a player. When I started FFR I was definitely in Division 1, by their standards, which would be somewhere between ranks 15,000 and 50,000 in osu!mania ranks. At that point, my dream was to one day be as good as those people AAA'ing the songs given to the D7 players in the 10th official tournament, especially people like Staiain. By the beginning of my senior year I had probably reached Division 4, not sure though, since I never cared to check, which would be around rank 4,000-6,000, maybe higher ranked than that, not really sure. When I started my first ever FFR tournament, the 11th official tournament, I was considered D5, which I thought was insane at the time. After the tournament, I had quickly skillboosted to Division 6, and, after more than 2 years of playing, I have reached D7 and can consider myself "Legendary" in FFRs terms. It has been 2 years and 4 months since I've started, and now I am who I once dreamed of being. Although I have a long way to go with how massive the skill ceiling for this game is, I am unbelievably proud of how far I've come.

As a player I am most amazed at my skill in Long Notes and SV's, both of which I was god-awful at four months ago. To put it in perspective, I used to think Figue Folle's Cruel difficulty had some of the craziest SVs ever and I couldn't even pass Strahv (the one used in MWC 4k 2016). I am happy to say that I have come far enough to have passes on almost any LN map that I have ever downloaded, even achieving S ranks on Voyage 1970, Morgenglut, and Mirage, as well as a 94% on Southern Waters Assault, and possibly the craziest, a 93% on True Millennium Queen (on scorev2 lol). My skill in SV I would consider to be my greatest skill, nearing top 10 on Evening's Singularity, top 3 on jakads' Aleph-o, and even a brief 1st place rank on Pope Gadget's biquette map, which I currently have 2nd place on (I am also pretty happy to say that I achieved the first 99% on that map).

I am currently in college, studying a Paper Engineering (I'm not going to explain it here, just look it up. TL;DR: I am learning how to make paper).
I am a rather good bowler, sporting an average somewhere around 220 - High game (289) - High Series (797)
On top of osu!mania and FFR, I also play Smite, used to play World of Warcraft (may try getting back into it soon), used to play Portal, Overwatch, maybe some other things I'm forgetting.
If you want to talk to me, it is perfectly acceptable to message me through osu!, or if you'd prefer, I also have a discord: TheToaphster#2613

I'd like to thank some specific people that have made my experience throughout FFR and osu!mania truly amazing: Nekos, Curestyl, Eona, Youre Salty xd, Zenith, Halogen, and I hope to add many more people to this list as I continue to develop as a person and a player.

Thanks for reading and being such an amazing community! I am beyond blessed to have had the opportunity to share the past two years with all of you, and to have improved at one of the most fun games I have ever played, even managing to break top 1000 here and top 100 on FFR!
May the upcoming times be filled with happiness and improvement!
Mania
(DF./)

10th Dan (95.45% on Luminal)

My milestones and goals:
[x]Hit top 50 US (08/29/2016)
[x]Hit top 1000 Global (09/26/2016)
[x]Hit 10000pp (Lol thanks DT pp) (03/05/2017)
[]Pass LN Tier X (I'd prefer a scorev2 pass(94.94 RIP))
[x]Pass Dan 10 (01/10/2017)
[]Pass Luminal Dan (Workin on it, should have it within a month of updating this (currently 03/16/2107) C'moooon Skillboost (FUCK 95.45!!!!!!))
[]Make Team USA for 4k MWC (Maybe? I'm right on the edge I think)
[]Hit top 500 Global (If I DT farm this is probably possible)
[]Get a map to ranked or loved status (lol I'm too lazy to do that)
[x]100 Replays Watched (I don't care if its a useless stat it's cool) (03/18/2017)
[]500 Replays Watched

The skin I use is just Staiain's skin with a few things edited, most significantly the LNs because the ones in Staiain's are too difficult for me to read.
https://www.dropbox.com/s/sfcamraw2iu3c ... n.osk?dl=0
Maps
Currently I have no ranked maps, but maybe that will change soon if I motivate myself to finish mapping and get modders for Oceanus :^)

Oceanus - cosMo@BouSouP - Has one finished difficulty currently, working on an EZ difficulty at the moment. Once it is finished, I plan on getting modders and attempting to get it ranked. Hopefully that goes better than I expect it to

Akasha - xi - Same as above, but this one's HD and EZ diffs won't be done for quite a while, at least until after finishing Oceanus and one other mystery map

MTC - S3RL - Probably won't be changing this very much unless I want to make it better, the second difficulty of this will more than likely be deleted soon, unless I actually want to try and get a LN map ranked, which would probably be a nightmare

Meteor - Shirobon - My first submitted map, not very good, might be subject to edits and extra difficulties in the future, but not for a very long time (Basically, don't play it)

Cheshire's Dance - a_hisa - Heavy LN map, pretty fun to me, though pretty uncomfortable in places (on purpose of course). Much happier with how this one turned out than MTC

perthed again (yambabom remix) - Mapping this was exhausting. Almost 2000 SVs were used, I don't even understand how Evening and Ciel do this so much. Will be edited most-likely, SVs are somewhat messy but still cool to watch and very fun to play. The finished product is definitely making me want to make more of this kind of stuff.

Dango Daikazoku - Chata - Not really much to say about this one, just decided to make a pretty chill LN map cuz I really like this song. Gives you the feels man, even to those of us who haven't watched Clannad (I finished it now, this song is now the embodiment of a feels train ;w;).

Pandemonium - xi - This was a guest difficulty I made for Youre Salty xd (the "Salty" from the collab). I fully created the 4k difficulty and the Svs in both the 4k and 7k difficulties. Maybe will have salty go for rank once we get a couple more difficulies.

WIPs:
Currently I have three maps that I'm working on, and all 3 of them are longer than 4 minutes long :^) kill me. Also, all three of them have different skillsets that they focus on.

Our Everlasting Dream - Helblinde - I'm mapping this because I listened to the song once and loved it. So I'm making a long note map out of it. Definitely not in the same difficulty range as Cheshire's Dance though.

Rapidity is a Justice - xi? - Also really like the song, but this one also seemed really fun to map, and will be jumpstream oriented, but does have LN elements in it.

Oselot - Alon Mor - Kill me. I'm making another SV map. This one I expect will be more difficult than perthed again, so watch out for this. Probably won't be finished and/or fully satisfied with the map until May or possibly even June, but I will finish it.
Standard
I use a Huion h420 tablet (I know, not the best, but it works), QW
side note: 100 pp club!1!1! We in there
